The paper deals with temporal logic and automata, which are topics that are commonly studied in the areas of logic (cs.LO) and formal languages (cs.FL). The use of linear orderings also suggests a connection to the area of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and the study of linear orders (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper's focus on reactive systems and decision procedures suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL).
